name: phase
doc: Phase shift in degrees

name: fmode
doc: reference frequency source: internal = 1; external = 0

name: freq
doc: reference frequency. Set only in Internal reference mode

name: ref_slope
doc: External reference slope Sine(0), TTL Rising (1) TTL Falling (2)

name: harm
doc: Detection harmonic

name: slvl
doc: Sine Output Amplitude

name: in_config
doc: Input configuration. A(0), A-B(1), I (2) (1 Mohm), I (3) (100 Mohm)

name: in_gnd
doc: Input shield grounding float(0) ground(1)

name: in_couple
doc: input coupling AC(0) DC(1)

name: line_filter
doc: Line notch filters Out(0), Line In (1), 2x Line in(2), Both In (3)

name: sensitivity
doc: Sensitivity to 2 nV (0) through 1 V (26) rms full scale

name: res_mode
doc: Dynamic Reserve Mode to HighReserve (0), Normal (1), or Low Noise (2)

name: tau
doc: Time Constant to 10 µs (0) through 30 ks (19)

name: filt_slope
doc: Low Pass Filter Slope to 6 (0), 12 (1), 18 (2) or 24 (3) dB/oct

name: sync_filt
doc: Synchronous Filter to Off (0) or On below 200 Hz (1)

name: ch1_disp
doc: CH1 display to X, R, Xn, Aux 1or Aux 2 (j=0..4) and ratio the display to None, Aux1or Aux 2 (k=0,1,2).

name: ch1_out_select
doc: CH1Output Source to X (j=1) or Display (j=0)

name: off_exp
doc: X, Y, R (i=1,2,3) Offset to x percent ( -105.00 ≤ x ≤ 105.00) and Expand to 1, 10 or 100 (j=0,1,2)

name: aux_output
doc: voltage of Aux Output i (1,2,3,4) to x Volts. -10.500 ≤ x ≤ 10.500

name: out_interface
doc: Output interface to RS-232(0) or GPIB(1)

name: gpib_override
doc: GPIB Overide Remote state to Off (0) or On (1)

name: key_click
doc: Key Click to Off (0) or On (1)

name: alarm
doc: Alarms to Off (0) or On (1)

name: save_setup
doc: save current setup to setting buffer

name: recall_setup
doc: recall setup from setting buffer

name: auto_gain
doc: Auto Gain function. Same as pressing the [AUTO GAIN] key.

name: auto_reserve
doc: Auto Reserve function. Same as pressing the [AUTO RESERVE] key.

name: auto_phase
doc: Auto Phase function. Same as pressing the [AUTO PHASE] key.

name: auto_off
doc: Auto Offset X, Y, R (i=1,2,3)

name: sample_rate
doc: DataSample Rate to 62.5 mHz (0) through 512 Hz (13) or Trigger (14).

name: scan_mode
doc: one-shot(0) or loop(1)

name: trig
doc: software trigger command

name: trig_start
doc: trigger starts scan mode No(0) or Yes(0)

name: start_scan
doc: start or continue a scan

name: pause_scan
doc: pause a scan. Does not reset a paused or done scan.

name: reset_scan
doc: Reset a scan

name: val
doc: Query the value of X (1), Y (2), R (3) or θ (4). Returns ASCII floating point value

name: disp_val
doc: Query the value of CH1 Display. Returns ASCII floating point value

name: all_val
doc: Query the value of 2 thru 6 paramters at once.

name: aux_input
doc: Query the value of Aux Input i (1,2,3,4) in volts. Insturment has 4 AUX channels

name: data_pts_ready
doc: Query the number of points stored in Display i buffer (1,2)

name: read_buffer
doc: Read k≥1 points starting at bin j≥0 from CH1 Display buffer in ASCII floating point

name: read_buffer_float
doc: Read k≥1 points starting at bin j≥0 from CH1 Display buffer in IEEE binary floating point

name: read_buffer_nonnorm
doc: Read k≥1 points starting at bin j≥0 from CH1 Display buffer in nonnormalized binary floating point.

name: fast_transfer
doc: Fast Data Transfer Mode On (1 or 2) or Off (0).On will transfer binary X and Y every sample during a scan over the GPIB interface.

name: start_delay
doc: Start a scan after 0.5sec delay. Use with Fast Data Transfer Mode

name: reset
doc: Reset the unit to its default configurations

name: id
doc: Read the SR810 device identification string.

name: local_remote
doc: Set (Query) the Local/Remote state to LOCAL (0); REMOTE (1); or LOCAL LOCKOUT (2).

name: clear_status
doc: Clear all status bytes.

name: event_status_enable
doc: Set (Query) the Standard Event Status Byte Enable Register to the decimal value i (0-255). *ESE I j sets bit i (0-7) to j (0 or 1). *ESE? decimal value i (0-255). *ESE I queries the byte. *ESE?i queries only bit i.

name: event_status
doc: Query the Standard Event Status Byte. If i is included, only bit i is queried.

name: serial_poll_enable
doc: Set (Query) the Serial Poll Enable Register to the decimal value i (0-255). *SRE I j sets bit i (0-7) to j (0 or 1). *SRE? queries the byte *SRE?i queries only bit i."

name: serial_poll
doc: Query the Serial Poll Status Byte. If i is included, only bit i is queried.

name: power_on_status
doc: Set (Query) the Power On Status Clear bit to Set (1) or Clear (0).

name: error_status_enable
doc: Set (Query) the Error Status Enable Register to the decimal value I (0-255). ERRE i,j sets bit i (0-7) to j (0 or 1). ERRE? queries the byte, ERRE?i queries only bit i.

name: error_status
doc: Query the Error Status Byte. If i is included, only bit i is queried.

name: lia_status_enable
doc: Set (Query) the LIA Status Enable Register to the decimal value i (0-255). LIAE i,j sets bit i (0-7) to j (0 or 1). LIAE? queries the byte, LIAE? i queries only bit i.

name: lia_status
doc: Query the LIA Status Byte. If i is included, only bit i is queried.

name: comm_error
doc: get communication error; for self testing
